afterSOLIDrevisionEHL.model

Class SimpleElement

  • java.lang.Object
    • afterSOLIDrevisionEHL.model.Element
      • afterSOLIDrevisionEHL.model.SimpleElement
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Requestable, java.lang.Comparable<Element>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    Book, CD, DVD

    public abstract class SimpleElement
extends Element
    Class whose instances represent simple elements that can be put in a shelf. Simple elements have a title, they are not sets (they do not contain other elements) and they occupy 1 unit of space in a shelf. Some examples of simple elements are books, cds and dvds.
    Author:
    (original) Daniel Gomes, Filipe Maia, Pedro Antunes, (revisionSOLID) Eva Gomes, Hugo Leal, Lucas Andrade

        public Element isOrContainsElementsWithTheSameTypeAndTitleAs(Element element)
        Checks whether this has the same runtime type and the same title as element; returns this if so or null otherwise.

        Since this class's instances represent simple elements, they do not contain other elements, this method checks only whether this is an instance of Element with the same type and title as element.
